HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 115
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Gordonsville High
School Tigers softball team upon winning the
2024 TSSAA Class A state championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true
champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, again proving themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and, as such,
deserving of the highest regard, the Gordonsville High School Tigers softball team captured the
2024 TSSAA Division I, Class A state championship; and
WHEREAS, the 2024 title marked back-to-back state championships for Gordonsville,
who also brought home the hardware in 2023, and the third state title overall for Coach
Jonathon Bush and the Tigers, who first won it all in 2014; and
WHEREAS, after winning the District 7 title and securing a number-one seed, the Tigers
blanked East Robertson 12-0 and squeaked by Jo Byrns 3-2 in 8 innings to win the regional
title; and
WHEREAS, in sectional play, Gordonsville defeated South Pittsburg 1-0 in a defensive
contest to earn a berth in the state tourney; and
WHEREAS, after arriving in Murfreesboro, the Tigers truly hit their stride, winning four
consecutive games to be crowned state champions; and
WHEREAS, Gordonsville walloped Halls 13-1 and blanked Wartburg Central 10-0 and
13-0 in consecutive match-ups to reach the championship game; and
WHEREAS, the Tigers proceeded to devour rival Jo Byrns in a run-rule 11-1 victory to
win the Class A state title with an astonishing 33-5 overall record; and
